article.description: — Jacob Davison had 18 points to lead five Eastern Washington players in double figures as the Eagles topped Idaho State 75-62 on Friday.
article.headline: Davison, Robertson lift E. Washington past Idaho St. 75-62
article.linkText: Davison, Robertson lift E. Washington past Idaho St. 75-62
article.story: CHENEY, Wash. -- — Jacob Davison had 18 points to lead five Eastern Washington players in double figures as the Eagles topped Idaho State 75-62 on Friday. Tyler Robertson added 13 points, Michael Meadows and Jack Perry scored 11 each and Tanner Groves had 10 for EWU (13-7, 12-3 Big Sky Conference). Robert Ford III had 16 points and nine rebounds for the Bengals (13-10, 8-6). Tarik Cool added 15 points. Malik Porter had 14 points and nine rebounds. The Eagles leveled the season series against the Bengals. Idaho State defeated Eastern Washington 68-63 last Wednesday. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
